<br>
P.S. You DO need a reagent to port to the planes, correct? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufaerwyndcorpserunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faerwynd Corpserunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 6:44:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help on resist gear info please!</span><hr size=1> For the wiz portal spells, yes you DO need a reagent.  I personally concentrated on svf, svm, svc - I didnt ignore the others of course but those seem to be the main ones for the planes IMO(at least for Hate and Fear- I dont fight in PoG and have only peeked into PoA).<br>
<br>
A couple relatively cheap items to look at are a Kunzar cloak, cloak of the icebear, Froggy crown, and assorted player made jewelry(hematite rings, jacinth jewlery etc).  If you are heading to Hate alot I would particularly recommend working on svm- alot of them seem to like to gflux.  While fun to watch its no fun being on the recieving end. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulenaddaranatar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lenaddar Anatar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 6:54:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help on resist gear info please!</span><hr size=1> Plane of Air requires a stone bought in the Erudin Library called a &quot;Cloudy Stone of Veeshan&quot; and cost around 200-250pp given faction and charisma.<br>
<br>
Plane of Hate requires a stone bought in the Neriak Cleric guild called an Innoruck (somethingorother) stone. I just had it and lost the name, sorry. Its under spells though. Not a problem. Usually an evil type has to buy these for you. Goodie-two-shoes need not apply. Price. About the same from what I understand.<br>
<br>
Resists. SVM is critical as a Wizard post 46. Mine hangs around 126 or so self. This has saved me more than I can remember. Other resists can be swapped out as needed but svm should be top of your list. At your range you will likewise want to watch you FR and CR for dragon raids.<br>
<br>
Blue diamond earrings and bracers would be a luxury but one worth looking into. Saw one bought from a vendor (just the diamond) last night.<br>
<br>
Oh and one last point. Do not bother with porting to the planes till your really comfortably into say 48. The higher the level the smaller the aggro. Learned this the hard way.<br>
<br>
- Len<br>
<br>
 <p>Lenaddar Anatar of Xev
(Lord of Wizardly Gifts from Tolkien) 57th Level Evoker

Chancellor of the Realm
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucassiusruneblaze.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cassius Runeblaze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 7:45:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help on resist gear info please!</span><hr size=1> <br>
Don't stress too much, the gear will come in time.<br>
<br>
CR/FR/MR are generally more important than PR/DR but its all good and I have different set ups for different mobs...<br>
<br>
Most I've spent on resist gear is 10.5k on a Dagger of Thex. So rare that its worth it though. <p>Cassius Runeblaze &lt;Avatars of Discord&gt;<BR>
lvl 56<BR>
Rodcet</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urealwing.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Realwing</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ultradbz.net/buttons/mybutton.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 8:32:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help on resist gear info please!</span><hr size=1> The stone you need for hate sold in the cleric guild is called. &quot;A Fugalion Soulstone of Innoruuk&quot; Or VERY close to that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  maybe no &quot;A&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucylynex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cylynex</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 8:53:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help on resist gear info please!</span><hr size=1> Try to find items that raise a resist like CR / FR / PR while simultaneously adding MR.  Most encounters you will find require serious FR or CR, so between fights you can usually swap stuff around until you have some nice gear which has both <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   But you want to try to maintain a simultaneous decent MR, since that is always useful.<br>
<br>
Cylynex Torchlooter<br>
Sorcerer of The Elders <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvahrakjlorjallag.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vahrak Jlorjallag</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 8:59:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help on resist gear info please!</span><hr size=1> You can find hate stones in the Neriak cleric guild.<br>
<br>
You can find PoS stones in the Erudin Library.<br>
(and it's PoS not PoA btw)<br>
<br>
Some good general resist gear is the blue diamond bracers, diamond mask, diamond rings..etc.<br>
<br>
The general idea for CR, FR, and MR as a first focus is good.<br>
There are a few mobs with the PR / DR like Trak and a mob or 2 up in PoS.  Save that Green Silken drape and Stein of Moggok.  Great for PR.<br>
<br>
Vahrak <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 9:55:32 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help on resist gear info please!</span><hr size=1> at 46 I wouldn't worry too much about resists just yet. One of the big determinations in resists is your level relative to mob level. At 46, any dragons or big mobs are going to land spells on you pretty much regardless of what your resists are. <br>
<br>
Save your money because good resist gear if expensive. You also want to get you int way over 200 so when you start swapping out resist gear you don't end up with 150int.<br>
<br>
Like most people have said, MR/CR/FR are the most important. DR/PR are only good for a few mobs or dueling necros. You should try to get enough gear to be able to get MR and one other over 100 unbuffed. In reality, you should be able to get MR/FR/CR 100+ unbuffed pretty easily. <p><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Evoker of the 55th Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br>
<i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i><br><span style="font-size: 10px; font-family: arial">Officer of Infinity Watch a Terris-Thule Guild</span><p>
<span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: arial"><b>Moordian Killbringer<br>Warrior of 26 Battle Scars</b></span><br><i>Dwarven LaMachine of Death</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usbrobin24.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sbrobin24</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 11:53:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help on resist gear info please!</span><hr size=1> Haha, I remember when I sold my Thex Dagger for 40pp. Sigh. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=6276.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=6243.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=6256.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=6256.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6256.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6256.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="r